## Phase 2: Dark Mode Contrast Fixes & Premium Effects

### 1. Dark Mode Contrast Refinement
Following the initial B&W conversion, some metrics and secondary texts (`text-neutral-500` and `text-neutral-400`) suffered from low contrast against dark backgrounds (`dark:bg-neutral-900`) during dark mode viewing. 
- Transformed these to semantic text properties (e.g., `text-muted-foreground`), dynamically ensuring highly accessible legibility regardless of whether the user visits in light or dark mode. Fixed this in `AIAgentPreview` (Action items), `ProjectManagementPreview` (Tags), and general metric labels across all Bento preview boxes.

### 2. Premium Spotlight UI Effects
To establish visual cohesion and an upscale design language identical to the vibrant Hero section:
- **Ambient Aura Integration:** Introduced a `radial-gradient` spotlight matching the Hero components directly into the backdrop of the `LandingFeatures` section, retaining the `var(--primary)` glowing aesthetic organically without conflicting with the foreground's monochrome elements.
- **Glassmorphism Base Upgrades:** Upgraded all structural Bento Box preview containers (`bg-card border border-border/50`) to a glassy, elevated state (`bg-card/60 backdrop-blur-lg border-border/40 shadow-sm`), enabling the atmospheric gradient lighting to softly permeate through the cards, cementing an extremely premium feel.
